    "narrative": "For April 7, 2026, the Ghost Ride the WHIP lineup is anchored by **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (74.79), both of whom benefit significantly from facing Civale in favorable conditions. **Mickey Moniak** enjoys an elite +14% park factor boost, while **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** capitalizes on the same matchup with an 11% boost against the opposing starter's xERA. **James Wood** (71.11) also provides immense value in the leadoff spot; his combination of order placement and favorable park factors makes him a primary engine for our R and SB targets. Meanwhile, **Corbin Carroll** (67.08) remains a must-start despite a difficult matchup against Peralta; his aggressive profile against a slow-delivery pitcher gives him a projected 92% steal probability, keeping him in the lineup to hunt the league's scarcest category.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved **Josh Naylor** (50.44), who fell just shy of the efficiency threshold required to displace our current starters. While **Josh Naylor** possesses a strong base projection, the 19% downgrade due to the skill of the opposing pitcher Eovaldi ultimately rendered him a marginal play compared to the higher-ceiling profiles of **Tyler Soderstrom** (60.98) or **Giancarlo Stanton** (63.57). We continue to emphasize efficiency to preserve our game caps, meaning reliable but lower-ceiling bats like **Max Muncy** (49.63) and **Kyle Karros** (45.96) remain on the bench as we prioritize the platoon advantages offered by **Vinnie Pasquantino** (69.46) against Williams.\n\nRisk remains localized around our C1 and MI slots. While **Gabriel Moreno** (49.97) is currently slated for the four-hole, his score is suppressed by a difficult matchup against Peralta. Similarly, **Jose Caballero** (53.75) is currently hitting out of the nine-hole; despite a decent raw projection, his score is dragged down by a -8% order penalty and a negative platoon split. We will monitor the lineup card for potential defensive replacements involving **Gabriel Arias** or **Travis Bazzana**, but for now, the data suggests maintaining our current configuration to maximize our 5x5 footprint. We are also keeping a close eye on **Brice Turang**, **Seiya Suzuki**, **Carson Williams**, and **Dalton Rushing** as they remain in the wings should any late-inning weather concerns impact the primary starters.",
